Hehehe; quite inflammatory, very creative, factually accurate as far as  the few "historical truths" cited (but cautious to report only the partial facts that support the authors' case, while ignoring the messy details that do not); and totally irrelevent, because it assumes that the US Government has a responsibility to be "nice," or even to be "consistent" and "reciprocal." It does not, and doing so in many cases would make it violate its' own charter and reason for existence.<P>I don't require the government of the US to be "right" or "benevolent" or "altruistic," I expect it to follow it's charter to operate:<P>"...establish Justice, insure domestic Tranquility, provide for the common defence, promote the general Welfare, and secure the blessings of Liberty for ourselvs and our Posterity..."<P>I don't see anything in there that says we have to give a wet slap about any OTHER nations' Justice, Tranquility, defence, Welfare, or Liberty.... "for<B>Our</B>selves, and <B>Our</B> Posterity..." that is the sole mandate.<P>So long as the US Government acts in the best interests of its own citizens and their eventual heirs, I'm quite happy with how they get there.<P> If we manage it while being able to maintain happy-happy-joy-joy relations with the rest of the inmates on the planet, great, but if not, oh, well. That's their lookout.<P>If it requires that we drop atomic weapons on the main war-materiel-producing centers of a nation that has attacked us, I'm up for that, too, so long as we can make it stick.<P>The world court is the biggest joke ever to be played by the human race upon itself... even the country in which is is seated does not abide by its rulings.<P>Somebody needs to look up the definition of "Sovereign Power" and come to grips with the purpose of having a nation that is one... and what has eventually happened to EVERY nation that abdicated that power...<P>Oh, and before anyone gets the wind up regarding that word "welfare" (especially in cross-posts from another thread); if that's what you think the definition of "welfare" is, you really need to get reaquainted with a dictionary... preferably one written contemporaneously with the document cited.<P>--------------------<P>Grunthos the Flatulent<BR>54th level Asgoth<BR>Poet of Kria
