<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I think people throw around 'terrorist' too much.<P>Terrorist: a person or organization who launches attacks deliberately designed to kill and terrorize civilians as a means of furthering or announcing their political, social, or economic ends.<P>By this definition, the USA is not a terrorist organization. We have killed civilains, that is true, and it's a common occurance in warfare, but we don't launch operations just to kill them. In other words, intent is crucial. We have always tried to kill combatants, not civilians.<P>To call the US a terrorist organization is a flat-out lie.<P>--------------------<P><I>Cowards die many times before their deaths. The valiant only taste of death but once.</I><P>-William Shakespeare, <I>Julius Ceasar</I>
