<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR> I'm curious how long we can keep our position of doing whatever we want simply because we can and nobody is strong enough to stop us. Very curious. <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Easy answer; about as long as France managed to hold on to their country once Germany decided they wanted it, and could take it (twice!)<P>Or as long as Israel would be able to keep their state, if they decided to forsake their use of military force.<P>The problem is this, there is only one swingset on this palyground, there are more kids arriving all the time that want a swing, and there are no teachers.<P>Who gets the swings?<P>Even if the big kids decide to band to gether, ignore their own interests in swinging, and enforce the taking of turns among all the kids, will this satisfy everybody?<P>What if there's one little kid that REALLY wants a swing, doesn't want to share, resents the big kids for forcing him to wait... and he's just found a nice sharp rock, and some like-minded little kids?<P><BR>Even if we "weren't insisting on doing whatever we want because we can," even if we were just minding our own business, leading our own lives, letting the rest of the world do what it wants (the situation, by the way, prior to World War I - - America's official foriegn policy was Isolationist), eventually somebody's going to decide that we really don't deserve what we have, and they should take it. Or that they don't like our friends. Or our beliefs.<P>If you want to be immune from attack, you must have nothing worth taking, do nothing worth opposing, say nothing worth listening to, express no opinions, and take no actions. And even then, like the Phillipines, you might just end up being in the wrong place a the wrong time.<P>Countries that have never been attacked from outside can be counted on one hand. And they are uniformly small, weak, neutral, inaccessible, and poor in natural resources.<P>And even that has not been a perfect defense - - ask a Haitian.<P>--------------------<P>Grunthos the Flatulent<BR>54th level Asgoth<BR>Poet of Kria
