<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>   <B>What will happen when other countries grow tired of what they see as American arrogance? When they realize that if "might makes right" they should be fighting against us with our own favorite weapon - violence. </B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>When America falls (and it will eventually, nothing lasts forever), another super power will arise (my prediction is China), and then every liberal in the world will have a new target to scream "you can't do that!" at.  In the same way super powers have been resented all through-out history (Rome, Autamen, etc.) now its are turn.<P>Where were the human interest groups, when Cambodian rebels were maiming, torturing, and killing their own people over a 10 year period, killing off eventually <I> one third </I> of their population?  Where were the protests, saying "Stop cutting open pregnant women with bayonetts, and ripping their unborn children out in front of their families!"<P>Answer:  They had nothing to gain by protesting that.  Their agenda could not be furthered in anyway.<P>In closing, I found it amusing that this news story told us that news stories are biased, and that the "other side of the coin" is usually right.  Following the authors own logic and advice, I should disregard the post completely, and write it off as inaccurate.<P>To break away from the thread for a bit, I'd just like to say that I grow tired of the number of posts, pointing fingers and saying "How dare America do this!", without offering a superior solution.  Any weak mind can point a finger and say "You Suck", but real problem solving requires the formulation of a solution that can be applied to the controversy at hand, and get better results.  I have yet to see any of those idea's here.  So keep whining away about "America this, and America that..." if you want.  But its not helping anything.<P>--------------------<P>Dominus<BR>Mith Marr<BR>58 Enchanter<BR>---<BR>Are you scared?
