Green, the best resource I know fo this kind of information is "the statistical abstract of the united states," which is published by the state department. Itere'sa copy in evry pbulic library; the latest I could find on-line in PDF was for 1999 (which means it covers through 1999)<P>Section 28 covers foriegn investment, trade balances, and aid.<P>Contained a few surprises for me, and probably will for you, too.<P>(Scroll to Table 1321 for foreign economic aid to countries, 1995-1997, and also see Table 1320 for foreign military aid to countries) <P><A HREF="http://www.census.gov/prod/99pubs/99statab/sec28.pdf" TARGET=_blank>Statistical Abstract of the United States; 1999, section 28</A><P>Seek the truth, for it shall set you free... and give you massive bleeding headaches...<P>--------------------<P>Grunthos the Flatulent<BR>54th level Asgoth<BR>Poet of Kria
