In response to your question, Green, I was think of a few, notably:<P> France (only got their country back for them, twice) <BR>Egypt (they get nearly as much aid from us as does Israel) <BR>China (saved their a$$ and protected them duing pre-WWI through WWII; although, to be fair, the government we helped was diposed by the communists during the People's Revolution, and now resides in Taiwan... and they appreciate us well enough, even if they don't understand us too well)<BR>Phillipines (Liberated them in WWII from Japanese occupation, rebuilt their country, build naval bases there (and paid for the privilege) that protected them and fed untold billions into their economy, only to have them void said leases and chuck us out once they felt safe... but now that the islamic militants are trying to depose their government, they're falling over themselves to be our buddy again... and, oh yeah, could you bring the navy back, please?)<P>There are others, but those are the ones that come to mind just now.<P>Hope that helps.<P>--------------------<P>Grunthos the Flatulent<BR>54th level Asgoth<BR>Poet of Kria
